The Police Service Commission (PSC) has promised to prosecute officers indicted for offenses during the 2019 general elections. The commission has resolved to officially write to the Acting Inspector-General of Police, Usman Baba on the matter. The PSC gave the hint at a meeting with some non-governmental organizations on the last national polls. Chairman of the PSC Fact Finding Team on 2019 Elections, Justice Clara Bata Ogunbiyi, announced that the commission was working to improve the safety of electoral processes. Ogunbiyi, a PSC Commissioner and a retired Justice of the Supreme Court, stressed the need for new strategies for an improved outing in 2023. She said the commission will investigate and hand over relevant files to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) for trial of election offenders. Rommy Mom, PSC Commissioner representing NGOs and Babatunde Dada, Legal Adviser to the Commission were members of the fact finding panel. Mom assured that the PSC will sustain the partnership with stakeholders in order to achieve effective policing during the next general elections.